<p><b>Chartreuse</b> is a <a href="/wiki/France" title="France">French</a> <a href="/wiki/Liqueur" title="Liqueur">liqueur</a> composed of <a href="/wiki/Distilled" title="Distilled" class="mw-redirect">distilled</a> <a href="/wiki/Alcohol" title="Alcohol">alcohol</a> flavored with 130 <a href="/wiki/Herb" title="Herb">herbal</a> extracts. The liqueur is named after the <a href="/wiki/Grande_Chartreuse" title="Grande Chartreuse">Grande Chartreuse</a> monastery where it was formerly produced, located in the <a href="/wiki/Chartreuse_Mountains" title="Chartreuse Mountains">Chartreuse Mountains</a>. The liqueur is nowadays produced in a factory in the nearby town of <a href="/wiki/Voiron" title="Voiron">Voiron</a> under the supervision of monks from the monastery.</p>
